						               													<description>Do you want to meet the great leaders of history?  Players can embark on a real journey through history from Antiquity to our times. It is possible to come across questions, anecdotes and curiosities in the journey of Alexander the Great to conquer the world, in the extraordinary kingdom of Ramses II or browse in the Empire of Genghis Khan. Without forgetting Giuseppe Garibaldi, the battles of Napoleon or the great Julius Caesar.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A of traps, cards and numbers. Also an intelligent way to discover or rediscover these great generals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Quiz with 6 categories of questions on the subject of the game in addition to Junior questions for children. Turn the cards over and find out which question category you will need to answer.&amp;#10;But watch out ... there could be the Unexpected card and off to the clash between the players to get the point!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game begins by choosing the dealer, then the player immediately to his left turns over a card from the category / contingency deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a category card is drawn, the dealer or another player takes a card from the question deck and asks the question based on the category drawn.  In case of correct answer, the player who answered takes the card (which is worth 1 point) and places it in front of him.  The player continues to draw categories / contingencies until he misses a question or until the unexpected card forces him to fold.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If an unexpected card is drawn, the player will have to do what the card requires and something positive or negative can happen.  For example, being able to steal a point from an opponent, choosing the category for the question but also having to give a point to another player, etc. etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to reach the required number of points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
